.\" termin.al-name: whoami
.\" termin.al-usage: whoami
.\" termin.al-summary: Show the current development capability.
.TH WHOAMI 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
whoami \- Show the current development capability.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
whoami
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Refreshes and prints the current anonymous, GitHub-viewer, owner and CV-viewer capability state. GitHub states include the authenticated login.
.SH FAILURES
Arguments are rejected. When authentication is unavailable, public browsing continues and the command reports anonymous authentication-unavailable status.
.SH NOTES
Identity is shown only in the terminal session and is not sent to site statistics.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ whoami
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
login(1), logout(1), cv(1), stats(1)
